section.section:
"Law enforcement officer" means:
a member of a police force or other unit of the United States, the State, a county, municipal corporation, or other political subdivision who is responsible for the prevention and detection of crime and the enforcement of the laws of the United States, the State, a county, municipal corporation, or other political subdivision;
a park police officer of the Maryland-National Capital Park and Planning Commission;
a member of the University of Maryland police force; and
any military or militia personnel directed by constituted authority to keep law and order.
